    <!-- END FEATURED WORK SECTION -->

    <!-- ABOUT SECTION -->
    <section class="py-16 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-xl font-medium text-gray-800 dark:text-neutral-200">
        About Pinsky Studio
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 max-w-2xl">
        Pinsky Studio is the creative practice of Bregy Malpartida, exploring
        the intersection of algorithmic processes, formal systems, and tangible
        art. Our work investigates how mathematical concepts and computational
        methods can be expressed through visual and physical mediums.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 max-w-2xl mt-3">
        Through a combination of custom plotter technology, traditional painting
        techniques, and digital processes, we create works that bridge the gap
        between the digital and physical worlds. Our practice is driven by a
        fascination with emergence, recursion, and the patterns that arise from
        simple rules applied iteratively.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 max-w-2xl mt-3">
        Each piece is an exploration of formal systems and their visual
        manifestations, inviting viewers to engage with the underlying concepts
        through both aesthetic experience and intellectual inquiry.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6">
        <a
          href="/connect"
          class="px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-gray-800 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 dark:text-white dark:hover:bg-neutral-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-neutral-700 rounded-lg transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-x-1"
        >
          Learn more about our practice
          <svg
            class="w-4 h-4"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"></path>
          </svg>
